SIMPLE: harvesting
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Harvesting
<hw>Har"vest*ing</hw>, <def><pos>a. & n.</pos>, from <er>Harvest</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Harvesting ant</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>any
species of ant which gathers and stores up seeds for food. Many species
are known.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The species found in Southern Europe and Palestine are
<spn>Aphenogaster structor</spn> and <spn>Aphenogaster barbara</spn>;
that of Texas, called <stype>agricultural ant</stype>, is
<spn>Pogonomyrmex barbatus</spn> or <spn>Myrmica molifaciens</spn>; that
of Florida is <spn>Pogonomyrmex crudelis</spn>. See <cref>Agricultural
ant</cref>, under <er>Agricultural</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harvestless</ent>⟦br⟧
